If the cases in the remote and local User Directories are mismatched as far as casing goes, synchronisation will fail.

The following may be found within {{atlassian-stash.log}}:

{noformat:title=atlassian-stash.log}
2014-03-11 01:00:10,951 WARN  [scheduler_Worker-4]  c.a.c.d.DbCachingRemoteChangeOperations remote group name [ dl-Int-services ] casing differs from local group name [ dl-int-services ]. Group details will be kept updated, but the group name cannot be updated
{noformat}

Replication process and workaround described on Crowd linked issue.

Stash 2.11 isn't compatible with MySQL driver versions less than 5.1 but this didn't prevent it from starting:

{noformat}
<database-information>
  <driver-name>com.mysql.jdbc.Driver</driver-name> 
  <driver-version>5.0</driver-version> 
{noformat}

